  • Method Details

    • deleteToken

      void deleteToken() throws RestException
      Deletes the unique access token identified in the request from the associate user's profile. It is optional to pass a token in the URL. If no token is passed in the URL it will attempt to delete any implied token that exists as a cookie, fingerprint, etc.
      Throws:
      RestException

    • deleteToken

      void deleteToken(Map<String,Object> queryParams) throws RestException
      Deletes the unique access token identified in the request from the associate user's profile. It is optional to pass a token in the URL. If no token is passed in the URL it will attempt to delete any implied token that exists as a cookie, fingerprint, etc. Note, this is equivalent to the other deleteToken method, but with the query parameters collected into a single Map parameter.

    • getToken

      TokenV4Response getToken() throws RestException
      By calling the Get Token endpoint a new access token is created. By calling the Get Token endpoint a new access token is created. Extole will attempt to detect who the advocate is (based on cookies, browser fingerprint, etc) and provide them an access token with the greatest number of capabilities possible. If Extole is unable to recognize the advocate the access token will only have the UPDATE_PROFILE capability available.
      Returns:
      TokenV4Response
      Throws:
      RestException

    • getToken

      TokenV4Response getToken(Map<String,Object> queryParams) throws RestException
      By calling the Get Token endpoint a new access token is created. By calling the Get Token endpoint a new access token is created. Extole will attempt to detect who the advocate is (based on cookies, browser fingerprint, etc) and provide them an access token with the greatest number of capabilities possible. If Extole is unable to recognize the advocate the access token will only have the UPDATE_PROFILE capability available. Note, this is equivalent to the other getToken method, but with the query parameters collected into a single Map parameter.
      Parameters:
      queryParams - Map of query parameters as name-value pairs

      The following elements may be specified in the query map:

      Returns:
      TokenV4Response
      Throws:
      RestException
